Quiz API 🧠
A simple REST API for creating, retrieving, and playing quizzes, built with Node.js, Express.js, and MongoDB.

Requirements 📌
Node.js (>= v14)

MongoDB (Local instance or Compass)

Postman (For testing API requests)

Installation & Setup 🚀
1️⃣ Clone the Repository
sh
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-repo-name.git
cd your-repo-name
2️⃣ Install Dependencies
sh
Copy
Edit
npm install
3️⃣ Configure MongoDB
Start MongoDB locally (Make sure MongoDB is running):

sh
Copy
Edit
mongod --dbpath /data/db
Update .env file with:

ini
Copy
Edit
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/quizDB
PORT=5000
4️⃣ Run the Server
sh
Copy
Edit
node server.js
or, with Nodemon (for auto-restart on changes):

sh
Copy
Edit
npm run dev
Available Commands
Command	Description
npm install	Install dependencies
npm start	Start the API server
npm run dev	Start with Nodemon (auto-restart)
mongod --dbpath /data/db	Start MongoDB locally
node server.js	Run the API manually
Dependencies Used 📦
Package	Purpose
express	Web framework for Node.js
mongoose	MongoDB ODM for managing database
dotenv	Loads environment variables from .env
nodemon (dev)	Restarts server on file changes
API Endpoints
POST /api/quiz/create → Create a quiz

GET /api/quiz/ → Get all quizzes

POST /api/quiz/play → Play a quiz & get score

Testing the API with Postman
Open Postman and create requests:

POST /api/quiz/create → Create a quiz

GET /api/quiz/ → Retrieve quizzes

POST /api/quiz/play → Submit answers

